DESCRIPTION:In 18th century Venice\, 20-year-old violin virtuoso Cecilia lives at the Pièta orphanage\, where\, despite her talent\, she remains confined\, knowing that marriage is the only way out. Yet\, her life takes a turn after she meets Antonio Vivaldi\, a brilliant and ambitious composer who becomes the new violin teacher. Guided by Vivaldi and his music\, Cecilia finds the strength to challenge the destiny that once seemed inevitable.
